cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.MA 

The paper deals with the problem of influence maximization in social networks and uses a mechanism design approach to elicit influence probabilities truthfully from the agents. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and models, indicating that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories.
